    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-24T11:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-24T11:29:00-05:00" n="396"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d396">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.85/73</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GWE1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-24T11:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 24, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 1.15 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your May 22, 7 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d396fn1">Not printed; see telegram of Apr.
                        29, 1917, 11 a.m., to the Minister, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_270">p. 270</ref>.</note> German ships, as previously
                    explained, have been seized and taken possession of by Government of Cuba. They
                    are prizes of war. There is no title of transference. President <persName
                        corresp="#p_MMG1">Menocal</persName> says Cuban Government is not
                    considering making money out of these ships and does not care sell to shipping
                    companies, if the United States wishes to use them it can have them on any terms
                    it wishes. If not he will have them used in trade between United <pb facs="0459"
                        n="287" xml:id="pg_287"/> States and Cuba. He has offers near quarter
                    million dollars per month rental.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GWE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
